definitions.definition: A small separate part or one of the compartments of a room , especially in a work environment.
examples: Most libraries provide cubicles for quiet study.

definitions.definition: A small enclosure at a swimming pool etc. used to provide personal privacy when changing.
A small enclosure in a public toilet for individual use.
